Therefore, when a man is unable to provide for his family, he is seen as a failure. This is why most men in Lesotho are reluctant to divorce their wives even when they are unhappy in the marriage. They would rather stay in an unhappy marriage than face the shame of being seen as a failure.

The second reason why men in Lesotho are reluctant to divorce their wives is because they are afraid of losing their children. In Lesotho, children are considered to be the property of the father.
